text.section:
The Secretary shall:
continually compare the needs of the units of the Executive Branch of the State government and of the private entities with the revenues that are collected;
prepare estimates of revenues that will be available for the State budget;
prepare any other estimates of revenues that the Governor requests;
study the revenue structure of the State;
evaluate the sources of State revenues; and
recommend to the Governor:
appropriate changes in the revenue structure of the State; and
new sources of State revenues.

section.section:
On the basis of the studies, the Secretary shall report to the Governor on changes that the Secretary believes would result in economy or efficiency or otherwise would be in the State's best interest, including:
elimination or reduction of State programs;
abolition of positions;
changes in procedures; and
reorganization or consolidation of units.
